The party demands that the findings of an SABC disciplinary process which cleared Hlaudi Motsoeneng of any wrongdoing be set aside. CAPE TOWN The Democratic Alliance (DA) has applied to the Western Cape High Court to rule that South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) group executive of corporate affairs Hlaudi Motsoeneng should not hold any position at the public broadcaster.The party demands that the findings of an SABC disciplinary process which cleared Motsoeneng of any wrongdoing be set aside.The DA also says Motsoeneng had severely damaged the integrity, credibility and stability of the national broadcaster.WATCH: The DA application to have Motsoeneng removed